Car Crashes Caused by Distraction¶

distracted= total - not distracted

In [72]:
df["distracted"]=df["total"]-df["not_distracted"]
plt.subplots(figsize=(15,15))
sns.barplot(x='abbrev', y='distracted', data=df, color='red', label='Distracted')
Out[72]:
<Axes: xlabel='abbrev', ylabel='distracted'>

Conclusion- We can see that Washington Dc(DC) has negligible car crashes caused due to distraction whereas more than 95% of car crashes in Mississippi(MS) are due to distraction.

In [77]:

Out[77]:

Conclusion- Car Crashes happening for the first time increase as total number of crashes increase.

Profit Earned by Insurances in every state¶

Insurance Profit = Insurance Premium - Insurance Loss

In [79]:
df["ins_profit"]=df["ins_premium"]-df["ins_losses"]
plt.subplots(figsize=(15,15))
sns.barplot(x='abbrev', y='ins_profit', data=df, color='green', label='Profits')
Out[79]:
<Axes: xlabel='abbrev', ylabel='ins_profit'>

Conclusion- Washington Dc(DC) and NewJersey (NJ) have made most profits whereas Iowa(IA) have made least profits
